.mso pca.tmac
.TL
Some constants
.SH
Mathematical
.LP
\[*p] =
.eval
-- following prints pi, because cos(pi) = -1
troff:write(math.acos(-1))
troff:write('\n')
.endeval
.PP
e =
.eval
troff:write(math.exp(1))
troff:write('\n')
.endeval
.PP
\[*f] =
.eval
troff:write((math.sqrt(5)+1)/2)
troff:write('\n')
.endeval
.PP
\fIi\fP =
.eval
troff:write('\\[sqrt](\\[mi]1)\n')
.endeval
.SH
Weights & measures
.LP
1 oz =
.eval
troff:write((1/16) * .45359237 * 1000)
troff:write(' g\n')
.endeval
.PP
1 gal =
.eval
troff:write(231 * math.pow(2.54, 3) * (1/1000))
troff:write(' L\n')
.endeval
.PP
1 nmi =
.eval
troff:write(1852 * 100 * (1/2.54) * (1/12))
troff:write(' ft\n')
.endeval
.PP
1 phoot\** =
.eval
troff:write(.299792458 * 100 * (1/2.54) * (1/12))
troff:write(' foot\n')
.endeval
.FS
A phoot is the distance traveled by a photon in 1 second, i.e., a
light nanosecond. (N. David Mermin)
.FE
